sessions.title: Asexual Furs Meet and Greet
sessions.description:
Meet other fellow Asexual furs and contribute to how you accepted being Asexual from experiences and reading studies and what it mean to be Ace and/or on the Ace spectrum
Allies are welcome and encouraged!

sessions.title: Fursuit Dance Competition Preliminaries
sessions.description:
These are the closed door preliminaries for the Fursuit Dance Competition. If you are planning on dancing in the main event later on, you MUST attend this panel! No attendance outside of dancers/handlers is permitted.

A waiver form, along with parental consent for minors, will have been emailed to you, and need to filled out prior to the auditions. Please be sure to bring that with you to this panel.

sessions.title: Intro to Furry Fandom
sessions.description: Are you a casual observer of Furry Fandom? Or a brand new participant?  This basic introduction explains Furry Fandom in the broadest possible sense, its structure, internal culture, and other aspects!

sessions.title: Meet The Charity
sessions.description: Furnal Equinox is proud to be supporting Procyon Wildlife Rehabilitation and Education Centre as our charity this year! Their goals are to rescue, rehabilitate and safely release these animals, and to promote public appreciation for wildlife preservation. Come meet the representatives, get to know more about what they do and how you can help.

sessions.title: Pas Le Choix de Danser Auditions
sessions.description:
These are the closed door auditions for Pas Le Choix de Danser. If you are planning on dancing in the main event later on, you MUST attend this panel! No attendance outside of dancers/handlers is permitted.

A waiver form, along with parental consent for minors, will have been emailed to you, and need to filled out prior to the auditions. Please be sure to bring that with you to this panel.

sessions.title: Pok√©mon Go Meetup!
sessions.description: Trainers!  Come gather to meet fellow trainers from across the globe to share friend codes, conduct some trades, and share knowledge with other players!  Whether you're a beginner or expert, come join us for some fun!

sessions.title: Intro to Gender Exploration
sessions.description: Whether you find yourself unsure of your gender identity or are looking for ways to strengthen it, this casual excursion into what defines gender and the ways people express it aims to help with both a presentation and Q&A.

sessions.title: Fursuit Masquerade Rehearsals
sessions.description: Closed door: No peeking under the waves, this is our invite only closed door masquerade rehearsal.

sessions.title: Your First Furry Convention
sessions.description: Welcome to your first furry convention! If you're new and would like to know what exactly is going on and how to make the most of it, this is the panel for you! We'll have a few ice breakers, go over the basics of con rules, do's and don'ts, talk about what to expect, and how to have a blast!

sessions.title: Mario Kart - Open Gaming
sessions.description:
Location: Table(s) #TV4 - Pier 5 section of the Lounge.

The classic Nintendo kart racing game! Exact title to be determined.

Seating Limited on a first come, first serve basis.

This game is open for anyone to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the tables specified above, check-out a Mario Kart title at the Lounge's Checkout Desk and use the table(s) specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: Writing Wolf's Journey
sessions.description: Are you interested in writing in furry? I have been woring on a multi year webcomic and I will delve into the world on how to create and build a comic.

sessions.title: Meet The Guests Of Honour
sessions.description: Come by, moor your boats, and meet this year's aquaterrific Guests of Honour, and bring your questions along for a Q&A!

sessions.title: Canine Furries Meet'n'greet
sessions.description: Come socialize with your fellow woofers, barkers, and howlers. All good dogs welcome for a casual meet and greet session!

sessions.title: Cutthroat Artist
sessions.description: Cutthroat Artist pits 4 artists against each other in a series of hectic art challenges with only 10 minutes on the clock. With frantic bidding on art sabotages they can unleash on each other, who will make it to the dread charity bonus round?

sessions.title: Being a minor in the fandom
sessions.description: Are you a young person or minor looking to find your place in the fandom at a young age? Maybe a parent or guardian trying to figure this weird "furry" thing out? If so this is perfect for you! We'll be discussing ways to find your community, how to make friends, and most importantly how to stay safe at a vulnerable age. I will also be taking questions and giving personalized advice

sessions.title: Furry Karaoke!
sessions.description: Sing until your lungs give out! Join Darby and bring your favourite tunes for this fun sing-along karaoke-filled evening!

sessions.title: Magic the Gathering for Beginners
sessions.description:
Location: Tables B1 to B4 in Pier 4/5
Join us for a teaching and learning session for the card game Magic: The Gathering! Jumpstart packs will be available for players to build decks and learn to play, either lent out or kept at a small cost. Any experience level of player welcome to attend, learn or help teach.

Limited to sixteen(16) participants! First come, first serve.

sessions.title: Finances: Beyond the Basics
sessions.description: Go beyond the basics of finances to really kick off your financial independence journey

sessions.title: Uno Deluxe - Open Game
sessions.description:
Location: Table #1 - Pier 4 section of the Lounge.
"The classic card game where players match by color or number, trying to be the first to get rid of all the cards in their hand. When players are down to one card, they must yell "UNO!" for the win."

2 - 10 players. Seating limited on a first come, first serve basis.

This game is open for anyone to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the table(s) specified above, check-out Uno Deluxe at the Lounge's Checkout Desk and use the tables specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: Dragon Tails and Scales of Ontario
sessions.description: Are you a dragon? a Kobold? an alligator etc any time of scale-sona. then com eon down to Dragon Tails and scales. It's the year of the Dragon so in the first half will be our meet and greet portion. second half will be the year of the Dragon group photo. If interested come on down and give us a peep. All scalies are welcome

sessions.title: Practical Furry Photography
sessions.description:
Tips on photographing fursuiters, getting better pictures, and overcoming the unique challenges of taking photos at a convention‚Äîthat anyone can use! 

I have been photographing fursuiters for 15 years, and I want you to know that no matter what equipment you have, you can take good photos.

Bring your smartphones, DSLR / mirrorless and compact cameras! You can also try a DSLR or mirrorless camera if you don't have one. 

There will also be some time for hands-on practice at the end! (Fursuiter and non-suiter volunteers wanted as photography subjects.)

sessions.title: Therianonthropy
sessions.description: A panel in which those who wish to learn the more hidden side of the furry world as a Therian and understand what it is or how it affects us day to day.

sessions.title: Super Smash Brothers - Open Gaming
sessions.description:
Location: Table(s) #TV1 & TV2 (as needed) - Pier 4 section of the Lounge.
Nintendo's Super Smash Brothers! Exact title to be determined.

Limited seating on a first come first serve and drop in/drop out basis.

This game is open for anyone to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the tables specified above, check-out a Super Smash Brothers title at the Lounge Checkout Desk and use the table(s) specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: Fursuiting Health
sessions.description: Fursuiting is a lot, but what if we could make it easier on ourselves? I'll talk about the things we can do before, during, and after fursuiting that will help you fursuit longer, recover faster, and get you back into your fluffy carpet sooner! Whether you're a newbie or someone who's been suiting for a while, come and learn how to better take care of what's under the colorful capet of fur! Got your own experiences and recovery methods? Come share them!

sessions.title: Rodents!
sessions.description: Come all ye gnawers and those in need of a good chew!  We will be celebrating the wonderful world of rodents with personal stories, fun facts, and good friends.  We will also have photo opportunity for all Rodent fursuiters at the end.

sessions.title: You, Me & DND
sessions.description:
An interactive, crowd participated version of D&D.
The crowd will all help run one character through a oneshot.

sessions.title: Pas Le Choix de Danser - Early Access
Pas Le Choix de Danser
sessions.description:
You've heard of Battle Zoo and Furgrounds, maybe you've even seen a Floor Wars or two, but are you ready to catch some PCD? Join your hosts Avalanche and Gnaw for Furnal Equinox's first ever head-to-head dance battle event, Pas Le Choix de Danser! This is a new an unique spin on this style of event popular at other fur-cons, featuring dancers showing off all their best moves for the crowd and judges to be crowned the PCD Champion. 

For our first ever Pas Le Choix de Danser event, we'll be featuring our DJ Guest of Honour Avian Invasion, who will be spinning up all the tracks for our dancers live!

(Please also note that anyone interested in competing in this event MUST attend the closed Pas Le Choix de Danser Auditions panel!)

sessions.title: Seaside Jeopardy!
sessions.description: The only thing vaster than the ocean is the depth of knowledge that humanity has accumulated.  You will need to tap that knowledge if you wish to succeed in a high seas battle of brains in this classic answer & question contest.  Some high culture, pop culture and careful wagering will allow your ship to come in as this year‚Äôs Jeopardy! champion.  Returning this year will be our team play format where the three contestants who pass the pre-game trivia challenge will have to pick a partner from the audience, so either bring a trusted ally or be prepared to form an uneasy alliance!

sessions.title: Pokemon Card Trading panel
sessions.description:
Location: Tables C1 to C5 in Pier 4/5.

Searching for the missing Blastoise for your collection? Have 2 extra Zapdos cards your looking to trade for Articuno and Moltres? Got a surplus of common/uncommon cards you wish to give away? Load up your binders with cards you wanna trade and let's do what the name implies: Trade some Pokemon cards!!

sessions.title: monsDRAWsity - Open Game
sessions.description:
Location: Table(s) #3 - Pier 4 section of the Lounge.
"Those pesky monsters are at it again, and one of them has been spotted nearby! As a paranormal investigator, it's your job to sketch out this newest anomaly based on your witness' description, but be careful... they didn't get a good look, and it's up to you to fill in the blanks!"

3 - 9 players, first come first serve. 
Overview Video: http://alturl.com/pdunc

This game is open for anyone to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the tables specified above, check-out MonsDRAWsity at the Lounge's Checkout Desk and use the tables specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: A Beginner's Guide to Vending at Furry Conventions
sessions.description: Interested in vending at a furry convention? Join Apoxon as they share their experiences as a dealer at over 20 conventions. Topics will include where to start, what to expect, and helpful tips and tricks for a successful weekend.

sessions.title: Munchkin Tails and the Mat of Mayhem
sessions.description:
Location: Tables #1 and #2 in Pier 4/5
It's the Munchkin card game, but it has gone to the dogs . . . plus foxes, mice, and ponies; now with MORE MAYHEM!

Anthropomorphic animals have always been popular, from the beast-headed gods of Egypt to Mickey Mouse and Bugs Bunny today. Now you can bring them into the dungeon, fighting off foes like the Human Rights Activist, the Robot Vacuum, or even the feared Animal Control Enforcer. Use a Tail Flail or a Cone of Defiance as you work to be the first of your species to reach Level 10!

With the Mat of Mayhem in the mix, EVERY level, except lowly level 1, gets an in-game bonus of your choice!

Bring your own OFFICIAL Munchkin promo and bonus-giving items and show everyone you can be the munchkiniest munchkin that ever munchkined!

Seats limited; filled on first come, first serve basis to a maximum of 12 in up to two casual open games.

sessions.title: Eves Fursuit Hospital
sessions.description: Learn some basic stitches to repair your fursuit on your own. Small repairs done on the spot by myself, Eve SewingStuffs for charity donations

sessions.title: Fur-Eh The Musical! Screening
sessions.description: Fur-Eh The Musical is coming to Furnal Equinox! Join Scout, or Dancer #2, as he shares a screening of the musical that dazzled Fur-Eh last July. A discussion/QA with any cast/crew members present may follow!

sessions.title: 85 Years of Fan Convention History (Including Furry Cons)
sessions.description: From the first multi-day fan event Worldcon in 1939 to the multi-media giants that swarm the convention halls of today, the evolution of pop culture cons have come far. From the filk of old scifi, to first comic con artist alleys, to the first AMV at an anime con, to the first fursuit parade at a furry con, to hand Trekkies and bronies had in innovating convention staffing, all of us are part of one large family tree of fan events. Presented by the Convention History Project.

sessions.title: BDSM101
sessions.description: Overview of the BDSM community, key safety considerations, and how to find your local community to further your kink education at home!

sessions.title: The Vore Panel
sessions.description: What is vore? Why do people enjoy being swallowed alive? More importantly, why is it in every cartoon and piece of media? Come learn and laugh with this comedic and informative presentation hosted by Marshmallow, with games, vore furs, and more!

sessions.title: Bovine meet
sessions.description: Meet fellow bovine furries within the community!

sessions.title: 'To Change' Tabletop RPG Session (TF/TG game)
sessions.description:
Location: Table #9 in Pier 4/5
To Change is a rules-light TTRPG where players will find themselves faced with a shared experience of a transformation in the body and mind. Whether the change is something terrible to be avoided or something wonderful to be pursued, whether it is something enigmatic or anticipated, the possibilities are limitless. 

This TTRPG game is centered around TF media a common and very furry adjacent interest.

sessions.title: Cards Against Humanity - 18+ Open Game
sessions.description:
Location: Tables A1 to A5 - Pier 5 section of the Lounge.
"The fill-in-the-blank party game that turns your awkward personality and lackluster social skills into hours of fun! Wow."

4 - 20 Players on a first come first serve, drop in/out basis.

This game is open for adults (18+) to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the tables specified above, check-out Cards Against Humanity at the Lounge's Checkout Desk and use the tables specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: Babyfur & Ageplayer Meet 'n Greet
sessions.description: Babyfurs, lil‚Äôfurs, caregivers and their bigger friends alike are invited to get together for some friendly cub chatter!  Bring your plushies and come reconnect with your friends, meet new ones and enjoy some colouring and other cub-friendly activities!

sessions.title: (First Slot) Friday Dance
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Puppy/Pet Play 101
sessions.description: Have you ever wanted to be a puppy? Have you ever felt like just barking at something or someone? Ever want to get down on all fours and chase around a ball? Or ever just been fascinated with a squeaky toy? Then unleash your inner pup and join us as we explore the wonderful and ever-growing world of pup/pet play. We will take you on a journey into the mind of a pup/pet as we discuss and answer the questions of - What is pup/pet play? Where did it all start? How are puppies and furries different? How are they similar? Why become a pup/pet? What is headspace? What is a handler and what do they do? How do I get started/involved? We'll also cover important safety aspects, basic etiquette, guidelines to follow, and the gear you may see.

sessions.title: Telestrations: After Dark - 18+ Open Game
sessions.description:
Location: Table(s) #10 - Pier 4 section of the Lounge.
"Everything's better after dark! Our favorite party game is all grown up. Telestrations After Dark is the adults only version of the #1 party game Telestrations. Draw what you see then guess what you saw for hilarious, weird, irresponsible and just plain wrong outcomes. Telestrations After Dark is "adults only" miscommunication at its best!"

4 - 8 adult (18+) Players on a first come, first serve, drop in and out basis.

This game is open for anyone (18+) to join and is not led by a dedicated host; If upon arrival there is no active game at the tables specified above, check-out Telestrations: After Dark at the Lounge's Checkout Desk and use the table(s) specified. Thank You.

sessions.title: How to Make an Adult Fantasy Toy
sessions.description: From the creator of Vancouver-based toy maker KnottyBoyToys, we will explore the process, tools, and considerations for designing and making a fantasy adult toy. There will be a display and demonstration of the equipment involved.

sessions.title: Fursuit Games
sessions.description: Join us for our annual friendly competition among fursuiters. The most fun you'll have under or over, beside or around, and every other preposition you can imagine regarding the sea. Full and partial suits welcome!

sessions.title: Kemono meet and greet
sessions.description: Are you a fan of kemono art and fursuits? Then this event might be for you! Hang out, chat, take some photos, and meet your fellow enjoyers of kemono!

sessions.title: Supersponsor+ Luncheon
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Furry Producers & Musicians Meet and Greet
sessions.description: A panel wherein furry musicians and music producers can meet each other, socialize, and share our work. Come one, come all, make friends to make beautiful music with! Music fans welcome as well, everyone loves new listeners and here's a place to find out what the musicians of Furnal Equinox have to offer!

sessions.title: How to Finance your Furry Fascination
sessions.description: Would you like to easily save 250$ for every furry convention you will ever attend? Would you like to never have to worry about your budget when buying furry stuff? Managing your money doesn't have to make you miserable, come on down for a presentation so easy that even a simple moose can understand it!

sessions.title: Women of Furry Meetup
sessions.description:
Come and be social with other women in furry. We welcome trans women, cis women, and non-binary persons interested in the woman's experience. Hosted by Women of Leadership in the Furry Fandom (WoLFF).
We are a group for trans women, cis women, and non-binary persons interested in the woman's experience, who take on staffing and volunteer roles at furry conventions and non-profit organizations, offering support, advice, and friendship.

sessions.title: Learn 2 Play: Creature Comforts:
sessions.description:
Location: Table #1 in Pier 4/5
Welcome to Maple Valley. The snow has melted and Spring has returned to to the forest. Everyone is enjoying the warm weather, but it's never too soon to start preparing for next Winter. 

In Creature Comforts you will collect resources to craft comforts to get you through the cold months to come. Who will have the coziest den when the snow comes again?

1 - 5 Players on a first come first serve basis.
Overview Video: http://alturl.com/qr7oi

sessions.title: Tour De Fur Muster
sessions.description: Gather in Frontenac for the Tour De Fur, scheduled to depart at 1pm

sessions.title: This Was In MY Game?! Cut Content in Retro Games!
sessions.description: Be amazed at the surprises lurking within the depths of your favorite retro games! Join Rick Fox, co-admin of the popular gaming website The Cutting Room Floor, as they take you on a modern day archaeological dig to unearth surprising things that you never would have guessed were lurking in your favorite games and obscure classics! Debug modes? Check! Unused graphics? Check! Game prototypes?! Double check! You'll never look at video games the same way again!

sessions.title: Tour De Fur Fursuit Walk
sessions.description: Join us on a scenic tour of Toronto's historic waterfront! Prepare to wave to many passers by and get ready for some gorgeous photo opportunities as we strut our stuff along the waterfront!

sessions.title: Turning Your Art Into A Business - Part 1 of 3: The Basics
sessions.description: Music producer, author, and voice actor Matthew Ebel (aka Avian Invasion) kicks off a three-part panel series with the essentials for turning your artistic passions into a full-time job: Setting up shop and not going broke.

sessions.title: Professional Character Design for Dummies
sessions.description: Join animation professional RoxxyRogue as she goes through the ins and outs of what makes for great character designs. Get a taste of what lies beyond the veil of industry standard and see if this is the career for you.

sessions.title: Virtual Pet Meet Up
sessions.description: Neopets? Tamagotchi? Flight Rising? Any sort of virtual pet game is welcome here. A great chance to make friends who also love raising little virtual friends.

sessions.title: Amazing Inflatables!
sessions.description: Ever see those cute big inflatable animals online around in the fandom and think "Hey, those look like alot of fun!"? Well we are returning the inflatable panel once again this year! This panel will have big custom-made inflatable toys from creators such as Puffypaws, WetnoseSqueak, PhenodToy & Inflatable World which you can come interact with, sit on or take photos with! Come meet some inflatable collectors of the fandom,  ask questions, get pictures, vibe and have fun!

sessions.title: VTubing and Content Creation
sessions.description: Looking to get into content creation? Look no further! Join CorgiCam and friends to discuss their stories, and learn the ins-and-outs of VTubing and creating content online!

sessions.title: Urban Homesteading 101
sessions.description: Come listen to one furry ramble about his journey learning foraging, scavenging, cooking baking and fermenting over the past four years!

sessions.title: So You're a First Time Pet Owner! Now What?
sessions.description: Are you a first time pet owner? Are you looking to adopt a pet any time soon? Do you have any concerns or worries about it? This meetup panel is open to participants of all these questions. Come share stories you might have regarding your experiences as a first time pet owner and give any advice for anybody looking to adopt a furry friend! Veteran pet owners are also welcome to attend and share stories and advice.

sessions.title: Xephyr & Anubis LIVE
sessions.description: Xephyr is the alternative hard rock band of Clumzy Lion, Cobalt & Turi the Dragon.

sessions.title: Pok√©mon TCG Tournament & Meet
sessions.description:
Location: Tables C1 to C5 in Pier 4/5
Looking for other Pok√©mon TCG payers? Want to trade cards or show off your collection? Maybe even learn how to play? Come meet fellow card game enthusiasts and enjoy the tournament.

Tournament will be held with decks featuring sword and shield and newer.

sessions.title: Those Darn Canadian Cartoons Turned Me Into a Furry!
sessions.description: Are you CANADIAN? Did you HAVE A TELEVISION SET in the 80s, 90s, or early 2000s? Were you INUNDATED with FURRY CARTOONS and LIVE ACTION MASCOT PROGRAMS, sponsored by THE GOVERNMENT OF CANADA (kinda, thanks grant system!) and now you're a FURRY?! You may be entitled to compensation... AKA, calling out what turned you into a furry in this panel lol. We were there. And now we're here. Time to yell about it!

sessions.title: Weasels of Myth
sessions.description: Weasels, Stoats, and Ferrets in Mythologies and Cultural Beliefs Across the Northern Hemisphere

sessions.title: Hyena Havoc
sessions.description: Meet and greet with the fandoms fellow hyenas! Come see other hyena fur suiters for pictures and learn about this charismatic species

sessions.title: VRChat Meet-and-Greet
sessions.description:
Plug in! Log on! Let's get virtual in reality!

Join us for our annual VRChat meet-and-greet! Whether you're brand-new to the VR scene or a longtime "Trusted User," join us to link up with friends from across the digital divide and chat about all the amazing things you can do in VRChat. Learn about everything from raves to games to chillout worlds. Experience all of the fun virtual groups of friends and furs you can meet along the way right here in reality. Join the right instance, and you can even learn about building your own world and avatar!

We are VR!

sessions.title: Asexuality in the Furry Fandom
sessions.description: What is asexuality? What does it have to do with being a furry? Join Darby as we explore the ace spectrum and discuss how sexuality can coincide with the furry identity. All allies are welcome!

sessions.title: Turning Your Art Into A Business - Part 2 of 3: Branding and Selling
sessions.description: Music producer, author, and voice actor Matthew Ebel (aka Avian Invasion) continues his panel series on how to earn a living from your artistic endeavors. Come learn how to hone your brand, set up a website, and learn how to deal with customers.

sessions.title: Hybrids meet and greet
sessions.description: This event will be an event where people who have a fursona that has more then one species built into the design of their character can meet and talk about why they decided to go for a hybridized fursona. Even so, anyone is welcomed. People who has 10+ species in their fursona or people who just have a single species fursona.

sessions.title: Fursuit Masqeurade: Early Access
sessions.description: Early seating for Supersponsors and those with Accessibility needs

sessions.title: Fursuit Masquerade
sessions.description:
Embark on a journey through a decade of dazzling performances as we proudly present the 10th-anniversary edition of the Furnal Equinox Masquerade! A celebration of artistic brilliance that began in 2013, this show has become a beacon for talent and creativity.

Past champions and fan favorites return to the spotlight, to create an amazing showcase highlighting thier skill and artistry. This isn't just a show; it is some of the most captivating talents that have graced our stage together for one night only.

Join us as we witness the triumphant return of past winners, alongside the rising stars who've consistently captivated audiences. The stage is set for an unforgettable night where passion, skill, and artistry collide in an epic all-star edition of the Furnal Equinox Masquerade.

sessions.title: Purple's TikTok fun !
sessions.description:
Since last year was a success, i'm making a another meetup of TikTok ! Come meet me and have fun with me ! Making tiktoks and making friends ^^ 
A group picture will be made during the event to immortalise it :) 
All are welcome !!

sessions.title: Shapeshifters & Transformation in Fiction - From Fables to Furry Culture
sessions.description: A look at the history and evolution of animal transformation in fiction, from early mythology to folklore and fables, from werewolves in cinema to modern day furry comics, transformation have played a role in countless morality tales, religious texts, horror fiction, henshin anime, to the fantasy genres. We will look at different narrative techniques, tropes, visual representations, and plots common with these works and ways they can be expended. This panel summarizes this long history and analyzes themes from these types of stories.

sessions.title: Kigurumi Making
sessions.description:
Join Apoxon as they deliver a walk-through talk on the basics of Kigurumi Making!

Topics will include converting measurements to a pattern, sewing techniques, and other useful tips and tricks.

sessions.title: Bird Meet
sessions.description:
Whether you are an Avian yourself or just like them.
Come on over and hang out! :>

sessions.description: Do you like party games? What about a party tournament? Would you like to play Mario Party the tournament

$20 entry fee, limited to 16 players, First come, First Serve.
Mixed Conspiracy and Conspiracy: Take the Crown draft. Packs first released 10 years ago, still sealed and ready for a two round draft. Packs awarded based on standings after 2 rounds, prize set will be recent.

sessions.title: Fursuit Care 101: Learn the basics
sessions.description: Just bought a fursuit? Curious about how fursuiters maintain their costumes? Listen as an experienced fursuit maker covers the basics of cleaning, storage and traveling etc

sessions.title: Transformation (TF) Meet and Greet
sessions.description: Curious about transformation and the TF Fandom more broadly? Well-established and wanting to meet old or new TF friends? Head on down to the TF Meet and Greet to meet like-minded transformation fans and chat with people who share your unique sub-interest(s), or bounce between different groups and get exposed to some fresh new ideas! TF triggers may or may not be included with the panel.

sessions.title: History of Furry Fandom
sessions.description: How did Furry Fandom get started? How has it been shaped and changed by each new generation of fans? A greymuzzle explains!

sessions.title: Step Up Your Groove
sessions.description: Making choreography is hard. Improvising dance is hard. Dancing...is hard! So come learn certain tricks and tips to create and elevate your moves, and even have a chance to show your stuff! Dancing clothing and shoes is highly recommended.

sessions.title: Comfort Characters: What A Hero Means to Me
sessions.description: Who is your favorite character that you take comfort in? Does this character do more for you emotionally? Come on in and talk about them. This panel is an open room meet and greet panel talking about characters (furry or otherwise) that mean the most to us. The room will be open where we will discuss our personal favorite "comfort characters," the individuals that give us a much needed pick me up in the face of anxiety. No character is off limits here!

sessions.title: Learn Toki Pona: The Language of Good
sessions.description: Want to learn a whole new language this weekend? Toki Pona is a minimalist constructed language that is like yoga for the brain. With only ~130 words and super simple grammar, you'll walk away from this panel with everything you need to know to read and write Toki Pona sentences. o kama sona e toki pona!

sessions.title: TFTuesday Podcast - Live!
sessions.description: Come on down to a live recording of the TFTuesday podcast! This podcast focuses on the concept of transformation, mainly in the niche of the furry community, and what the theme of transformation and interest in it means as it relates to its fans. Our live recording will delve into a few specific topics before taking some audience Q&As!

Learn how to maintain your fan base through social media, mailing lists, and VIP clubs (like Patreon) without burning yourself out.

Chevron is a gray wolf, gamer, and event host from New Jersey. He works with several VRChat-based convention groups like Tailbass, Misho's Feeshquarium, Vibe Night, SnelRev Events, Lords of Floof, and xCirrex Media to create events and bring people together for fun nights, games, friendship, and great times. He hosts Thursday VRChat Games every week, as well as in-person gatherings monthly, and passionately embraces VRChat and its rave and convention scene, especially with Furnal Equinox, CozyCon, and the Furality Online Xperience. You'll find him most often sharing photos on his art galleries to help promote his favorite events and organizations. Furrydelphia's first ever VRChat Meet-and-Greet and Intro Panel was co-hosted by TJCoyote, Chief, Chevron, and members of the Fluffy Fur Friends. Motivated by the Tailbass and Furality VRChat portals, Chevron is now working to set up VRChat portals and meets at other in-person conventions.

He serves as a Photographer for both Vibe Night and the Furality Online Xperience.

Chevron's love and passion for Furnal Equinox motivated him to cosplay as "Badgie" (Virtual Furnal Equinox 2021's unofficial mascot made of nothing but attendee badges) at the in-person convention in 2022. He would reprise his role in-person in 2023.

Chevron first attended Furnal Equinox in March 2021 over VRChat. The experience was so enjoyable that he dared to compared his experience at Furnal Equinox to Furality 2000 (November 2020). This motivated him to attend the in-person Furnal Equinox convention for the first time in March 2022. The trip was a first of many for Chevron: his first time in Canada, first time using Lyft, and first time public suiting. Chevron has now added Furnal Equinox to his list of yearly attended conventions.

A lifelong player of EVE Online, Mechwarrior, Armed Assault III, Halo, Command & Conquer, and Dance Dance Revolution, Chevron holds a particular appreciation for older games of the late 1990s-early 2000s, such as the first Ghost Recon (2002) and Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. His first video game was Mario on the original Game Boy when he was five years old. His admiration of cyberpunk and all things futuristic is on full display with his Illumi Cyberwear LED visor. His fursuit was made by Sarahcat. Outside of the fandom, he works in the IT industry as a cybersecurity administrator and is (jokingly) addicted to Mountain Dew.

Chevron's ultimate goal is to bring people together for fun and great times. He embraces the future with open arms and is eager to dive right into all the fun that can be had together with friends and the fandom.

speakers.bio:
My name is Daniel Walsh, but other furries call me Taque! I discovered the furry community when I was in air cadets back in 2015 and was an active member of the Newfoundland Furry and Anthro Society during grade school.

I recently moved to Montreal for work and was looking to get involved with local furry groups, that is when I attended my first furry convention Canfurence 2022. I was very anxious about attending as I didn‚Äôt know anyone at the convention and was overwhelmed when exploring the venue. The attendees of the furry convention were very friendly and showed me how to enjoy the convention to the fullest! Since then I‚Äôve been hooked on attending furry conventions and meeting new and experienced furs along the way!

I had a blast attending Furnal Equinox 2023, and being a guest panel speaker at Canfurence‚Äôs ‚ÄúYour First Furry Convention‚Äù panel. I have been grateful that the furry community is full of accepting and friendly people. I would like to share my experiences to help new attendees enjoy furry conventions, just like how other experienced attendees helped me!
